# What is markdown?
Markdown is a way to customize text on webpages. These customizations allow you to change the size, font, color, style and type of text.
this could be very useful in creating unique webpages and can play a vital role in how good a website will look and function.

# Github pages:
1. makes it very easy to publish webpages by elementating the technical aspect of creating a webpage.
2. there is lots of customization available for github pages such as themes and different styles of webpages.

# Github markdown syntax
1. header sizes are detrermined by the amount of (#) placed before the header
2. the fewer (#) the bigger the header will be
for example: largest header(#) 
             smaller header (###) 
syntax is advanced settings for text on webpages.             
